<subSubSection id="9EB8539FFFF8FF8AFFF8FF13D17D8FAA" pageId="4" pageNumber="350" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D61D0014FFF8FF8AFFF8FF13D17D8FAA" blockId="4.[151,1437,152,1572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis id="E4D6DC06FFF8FF8AFFF8FF13D52A8FE3" bold="true" box="[151,276,152,179]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Pronotum subquadrate, with denticles throughout the median carina of pronotum (
<figureCitation id="4E991C91FFF8FF8AFBBEFF12D1108FE3" box="[1233,1326,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); anterior margin of median carina truncated, with perpendicular projection over the head, provided with three protuberances (
<figureCitation id="4E991C91FFF8FF8AFFCFFF6BD4C68FAA" box="[160,248,224,250]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) and wavy (two conspicuous curves) (
<figureCitation id="4E991C91FFF8FF8AFDC8FF6BD6C18FAA" box="[679,767,224,250]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
, dorsal view); wings slightly longer than pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9EB8539FFFF8FF8AFFA8FE89D5688AE7" pageId="4" pageNumber="350" type="description">
<paragraph id="D61D0014FFF8FF8AFFA8FE89D1A38B1F" blockId="4.[151,1437,152,1572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis id="E4D6DC06FFF8FF8AFFA8FE89D69B8E4D" bold="true" box="[199,677,258,286]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">
Redescription (Female 
<typeStatus id="0919BEB6FFF8FF8AFEB3FE8FD67A8E4E" box="[476,580,260,286]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<figureCitation id="4E991C91FFF8FF8AFD3FFE89D6A88E4D" box="[592,662,258,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
):
</emphasis>
Body surface rugose. 
<emphasis id="E4D6DC06FFF8FF8AFCCFFE8FD7DE8E4E" bold="true" box="[928,992,260,286]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Head</emphasis>
. Lateral view (
<figureCitation id="4E991C91FFF8FF8AFBE6FE88D0DB8E4D" box="[1161,1253,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
): head and compound eyes inserted below median carina crest; protuberant and globose eyes with straight base; vertex and fastigium not visible between eyes; antennal groove situated below margin of compound eyes; facial carinae arched. Frontal view (
<figureCitation id="4E991C91FFF8FF8AFE57FEE5D5AD8ED8" box="[312,403,366,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
): fastigium of vertex straight; front hirsute; eyes laterally arranged on the head but not pedunculated; frontal costa inconspicuous, only the bifurcation and facial carina visible; two superior ocelli between facial carina; medial ocellus involved by facial carinae; antennal grooves placed beside facial carinae; antennae shaped as compressed segments laterally expanding from the base to the apex; left antennae missing; apex of each antennal segments with a lighter color than the remaining antenna; scapus and pedicel with small tubercles; maxillary palpi having the two last articles flattened and hirsute. Dorsal view (
<figureCitation id="4E991C91FFF8FF8AFCA4FD94D01B8D69" box="[971,1061,543,569]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
): vertex between eyes wider than eyes in horizontal and vertical diameter; supraocular lobe conspicuous; rectangularly shaped head. 
<emphasis id="E4D6DC06FFF8FF8AFA73FDC8D1AB8D0D" bold="true" box="[1308,1429,579,605]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Pronotum</emphasis>
. Macropronotal, rugose, subquadrate, erose, having irregular teeth and emarginations, with denticles throughout the median carina of pronotum. Lateral view (
<figureCitation id="4E991C91FFF8FF8AFDCAFD02D73C8DF4" box="[677,770,649,676]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
): anterior margin of median carina truncated, with perpendicular projection over the head, provided with three protuberances; median carina crest begins to decline after surpassing the apex of tegmina and then becomes thinner; prozonal carina and extralateral carina inconspicuous; ventral sinus and tegminal sinus present; lateral lobe almost truncated and slightly laterally directed; infrascapular area narrow, thin and shorter than fore tibiae; wings slightly longer than pronotum. Frontal view (
<figureCitation id="4E991C91FFF8FF8AFB88FC9CD17F8C61" box="[1255,1345,791,817]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
): lateral lobes of pronotum slightly projected and directed sideward. Dorsal view (
<figureCitation id="4E991C91FFF8FF8AFCB4FCB0D00B8C05" box="[987,1077,827,853]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
): median carina continuous and strongly elevated, with crested wavy (two conspicuous curves) (
<figureCitation id="4E991C91FFF8FF8AFC0EFCD5D78A8C29" box="[865,948,862,889]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1814,1839]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,179,1787]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Pictorial key to species of Lophotettix. Arrows in L. brevicristatus and L. zumbadoi indicate pronotum direction; in L. unicristatus the arrow points to the hook-like shape of the pronotum and in L. alticristatus and L. hancocki the arrow points to the shape of the anterior margin of the pronotum over the head." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491602" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491602/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig.7A</figureCitation>
), lateral lobe almost truncated. 
<emphasis id="E4D6DC06FFF8FF8AFA7FFCD6D4F98CCC" bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Sternomentum</emphasis>
. Inconspicuous. 
<emphasis id="E4D6DC06FFF8FF8AFEE9FC0AD5EC8CCC" bold="true" box="[390,466,897,924]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Wings</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation id="4E991C91FFF8FF8AFE86FC09D6008CCD" box="[489,574,898,925]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig.2A</figureCitation>
): tegmina and wings visible; wing longer than pronotum; tegmina ovoid and elongated with rounded apex; tegmina with slightly marked venation. 
<emphasis id="E4D6DC06FFF8FF8AFCC5FC2ED7D78CEF" bold="true" box="[938,1001,933,959]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Legs.</emphasis>
Hirsute. Fore legs (
<figureCitation id="4E991C91FFF8FF8AFBA7FC2ED17D8C90" box="[1224,1347,933,960]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2A, B</figureCitation>
): dorsal and ventral margins of femur with undulated carinae; tibias with two crests on dorsal margin. Middle legs (
<figureCitation id="4E991C91FFF8FF8AFA00FC42D4DF8B58" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2A, B</figureCitation>
): left leg missing; dorsal and ventral margins of femur with undulated carina, with a dorso-apical blunt spine; tibiae with two crests on the dorsal margin. Hind legs: both hind legs missing in the type. 
<emphasis id="E4D6DC06FFF8FF8AFB8CFB9BD1608B7B" bold="true" box="[1251,1374,1040,1067]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Abdomen.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="4E991C91FFF8FF8AFA00FB9AD4808B1F" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
): eight sternites visible, ovipositor valves short, superior margin of dorsal and ventral valve with small teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D61D0014FFF8FF8AFFA8FBD2D11F8BEB" blockId="4.[151,1437,152,1572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis id="E4D6DC06FFF8FF8AFFA8FBD2D6348B23" bold="true" box="[199,522,1112,1139]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Measurements (all in mm).</emphasis>
Body length from the tip of the frontal carinae to the end of the pronotum 15.96; pronotum length 14.91; pronotum height (from the lowest part of the lateral lobes to the highest part of the dorsum in lateral view) 7.30; pronotum width (dorsal view) 4, 75; fore femur length 3.42; fore tibia length 2.88;
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D61D0014FFF8FF8AFFA8FB4FD0088A53" blockId="4.[151,1437,152,1572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis id="E4D6DC06FFF8FF8AFFA8FB4FD67B8B8F" bold="true" box="[199,581,1220,1247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">
Sampling data (
<bibRefCitation id="B2337DE5FFF8FF8AFEEDFB4FD60D8B8F" author="Hancock, J. L." box="[386,563,1220,1247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350" pagination="387 - 426" refId="ref6804" refString="Hancock, J. L. (1909) Further studies of the Tetriginae (Orthoptera) in the Oxford University Museum. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London. Part III. 387 - 426. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1909. tb 02160. x" type="book chapter" year="1909">Hancock, 1909</bibRefCitation>
):
</emphasis>
“One specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="AEB54084FFF8FF8AFC56FB4ED7BE8B8F" box="[825,896,1221,1247]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, South America, collected by Bates; W.W. Saunders’ collection, presented by Mrs. F.W. Hope to the University Museum, Oxford.”
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D61D0014FFF8FF8AFFA8FA87D4D98A3F" blockId="4.[151,1437,152,1572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis id="E4D6DC06FFF8FF8AFFA8FA87D6768A77" bold="true" box="[199,584,1292,1319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Original coloration description:</emphasis>
“Darker, almost black body, (…) antennae black and pale annulate at the joints, (…) the middle tibiae pale annulate at the middle and margins little compresso-tuberculate; apical half of tarsi black.”
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D61D0014FFF8FF8AFFA8FAF3D5688AE7" blockId="4.[151,1437,152,1572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis id="E4D6DC06FFF8FF8AFFA8FAF3D58C8AC3" bold="true" box="[199,434,1400,1427]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Current coloration:</emphasis>
Similar to the original description but with fore and middle tibiae and second tarsus with brown markings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9EB8539FFFF8FF8AFFA8FA4BD5318974" pageId="4" pageNumber="350" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D61D0014FFF8FF8AFFA8FA4BD5318974" blockId="4.[151,1437,152,1572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis id="E4D6DC06FFF8FF8AFFA8FA4BD56C8A8B" bold="true" box="[199,338,1472,1499]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Comments:</emphasis>
This species is based on a single female specimen and the author did not designate the 
<typeStatus id="0919BEB6FFF8FF8AFA55FA4AD1A28A8B" box="[1338,1436,1473,1499]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">holotype</typeStatus>
in the original description. However, following the article 73.1.2 of ICZN that specimen is the 
<typeStatus id="0919BEB6FFF8FF8AFBBCFA6ED10B8AAF" box="[1235,1333,1509,1535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">holotype</typeStatus>
fixed by monotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
